      "text": "Scenario\n\nDesign a multi-region healthcare data pipeline that ingests, processes, and serves protected health information (PHI) for enterprise customers (hospital systems, labs, insurers).\n\nThe platform supports:\n        •        Batch and near-real-time ingestion (EHR exports, lab results, claims)\n        •        Multi-stage processing (validation → normalization → enrichment → aggregation)\n        •        Exactly-once processing semantics per logical data submission\n        •        Strict auditability and traceability for every data access and transformation\n        •        Role-based access control and least-privilege enforcement\n        •        Encryption at rest and in transit\n        •        Active/active regions with regional failure handling\n        •        Cost controls and retention policies\n\nThis is not a research system. It is production healthcare infrastructure subject to compliance audits.\n\n⸻\n\nNon-Negotiable Constraints (Given)\n        •        The platform stores and processes PHI\n        •        HIPAA compliance is required (assume audits)\n        •        Data lineage must be reconstructable per patient record\n        •        Tenants are isolated (logical + operational)\n        •        The system operates in multiple regions concurrently\n\nDo not assume:\n        •        Eventual consistency is acceptable everywhere\n        •        You can “just log everything”\n        •        Operators have blanket access",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario\n\nDesign a multi-region healthcare data pipeline that ingests, processes, and serves protected health information (PHI) for enterprise customers (hospital systems, labs, insurers).\n\nThe platform supports:\n        •        Batch and near-real-time ingestion (EHR exports, lab results, claims)\n        •        Multi-stage processing (validation → normalization → enrichment → aggregation)\n        •        Exactly-once processing semantics per logical data submission\n        •        Strict auditability and traceability for every data access and transformation\n        •        Role-based access control and least-privilege enforcement\n        •        Encryption at rest and in transit\n        •        Active/active regions with regional failure handling\n        •        Cost controls and retention policies\n\nThis is not a research system. It is production healthcare infrastructure subject to compliance audits.\n\n⸻\n\nNon-Negotiable Constraints (Given)\n        •        The platform stores and processes PHI\n        •        HIPAA compliance is required (assume audits)\n        •        Data lineage must be reconstructable per patient record\n        •        Tenants are isolated (logical + operational)\n        •        The system operates in multiple regions concurrently\n\nDo not assume:\n        •        Eventual consistency is acceptable everywhere\n        •        You can “just log everything”\n        •        Operators have blanket access",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "hEITtSPhuv8s_k1AuJDGN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -3159.562913151981,
      "y": -2981.273481809145,
      "width": 1538.0516256582027,
      "height": 6525,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
