      "updated": 1770729805893,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements\n\nIngestion Job Definitions:\n    Create/Read Job (Batch/Near-Real-Time) Ingestion Definitions\n    Create new versions of job definitions; view prior versions\n    Support multi-stage processing( validation -> normalization -> enrichment -> aggregation ) \n    \nIngestion Run Definitions:\n    Submit run referencing a specific Job Definition version with input references\n    cancel a run\n    View/export run event history\n    Get Job Status + per-stage status\n    \nData Access:\n    Query patient records (Curated)\n    Query lineage for a patient record / run\n    Query audit data (who accessed what, when, via which action)\n    Produce Audit reports / exports for a time range and tenant\n\nData Purge Operations:\n    Apply retention policies\n    Execute purge by policy label / patient request\n\nTenant:\n    Create/manage tenants and their scoped resources\n    Manage roles/permissions (scoped to tenant)\n    Manage users/service accounts\n    view tenant configuration change history\n    View/export tenant usage and cost attribution reports    \n    \n\n⸻\n\nNon-Functional Requirements \nAvailability / DR\n    CP SLO: 99.99% (Create/Read Job, Submit/Cancel run, Query)\n    DP SLO: \n        * per cluster availability 99.99%\n        * per-logical-run target 99.999% w/ sequential failover\n        * Failure Classes: component / zone / region; degraded-mode preference: serve traffic > make changes\n    RPO/RTO (for control-plane state only):\n        Submit/Cancel persisted state: RPO 2 minutes\n        Config state (tenant/job): RPO 5 minutes\n        RTO targets: Submit/Cancel 2 hours; Config 6 hours\n\nScale / Geo:\n    Tenants: 100s\n    Job Definitions: 100s\n    Concurrent Jobs: 100s\n    Ingestion Rate(max / avg ): (100,000 / 10,000) records a minute\n    Payload Size(max / avg ): (10mb / 1mb)\n    Data Growth:  10,000 records a minute * 1mb = 10GB / minute\n    Exactly-once processing semantics per logical data submission\n    active/active regions with regional failure handling, multi-region concurrency\n\nLatency(p95 / p50): \n    Ingest-to-Bronze from Kafka: < 30s / < 1s \n    All Indexed Queries: < 1s / < 200ms\n    Job Scheduling: # Counts include non-failover events, +5 minutes for failover\n        SubmitJobRun: < 500ms / < 10ms\n        GetJobRun / status: < 500ms / 10ms\n        Enqueue-to-start (scheduler + dispatch): < 5s / < 1s\n        CancelRun: < 30s / < 10s\n\nSecurity: \n    Strong Authentication and Authorization for each tenant\n    RBAC controls per tenant user for data access; \n    Data is encrypted at rest and in transit\n\nAudit: \n    patient records and lineage(immutable, add (timestamp, user, and on mutation the data column version change))\n    Job and Run Definitions and changes(immutable, w/ timestamp, user, and version change)\n    HIPAA data access(immutable)\n    Data is tagged with Policy Labels for TTL\n \nCost:\n    data retention for all audit and definition by policy label\n    tenant cost show back and quotas \n\nObservability: \n    Golden signals (latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and globally\n    SLO burn-rate paging;\n    Timeseries Cost Spend Graphs per Job\n    Rollback triggers for jobs\n\n\n    \n⸻\n\nScope\n    Assumption:\n        Identity Providers are external\n        Electronic Health Records configuration are assumed to be understood\n            Long-term storage is object storage (provider-managed) and is the system of record for bronze artifacts\n        Out of Scope\n                * User portal, experimentation, producing data, data labeling per policy\n                * Building/testing job artifacts (CI/CD)\n                * Full centralized telemetry ingestion/storage pipeline\n                * Cost-center accounting system (we only produce usage/charge events)\n                * Multi-region concurrent execution of the same logical run (active/active execution)\n                * dynamic cluster registration UI/workflows\n                * Latency for Bronze-to-Silver & Silver-to-Gold is job specific and dependent on the curation workflow\n                * No automatic partial rollback of downstream curated datasets    \n        In Scope:\n            Ingestion from Kafka to Bronze bucket\n            Batch Job Processing from bucket to bucket    \n            PHI level Audit for ETL/ELT workflows\n            Explicits queries for ( patient records/lineage, job definition and execution, and user data access )\n            \n           \n    ⸻\n    \n    Correctness Invariants\n    \n    Tenant Isolation: Tenant-scoped data, compute, and quotas never cross tenant boundaries; all execution and attribution is strictly tenant-scoped.\nPrevents: data leakage, noisy neighbor incidents, incorrect chargeback.\n    \n    Single Logical Identity via Idempotency: For a given tenant and idempotency key, there is exactly one logical ingestion submission; retries must never\ncreate a second logical entity. Prevents: duplicate messages under retries and partitions.\n    \n    Immutable, Versioned Audit Log: All job definition versions, run lifecycle events, patient records, and HIPAA data is append-only within retention window\nand deletions are policy-driven and themselves audited. \n    \n    Authorization-before-access for PHI: User access controls with least-privilege are required access to data by policy of that data. \n    \n    Lineage completeness: Every served patient record can be traced within the policy retention window. \n    ⸻\n    \nAPI Surface \n    Control Plane(all client-facing):\n        1. Tenant & Identity/Access management \n                • Tenant Scoped\n                    • GET /tenants\n                    • PATCH /tenants/{tenant_id}/settings\n                    • POST /tenants/access # manage role bindings to users_id's\n                • Platform Scoped\n                    • DELETE /tenants/{tenant_id}\n                    • POST /tenants\n        2. Job definition management (versioned)\n                • POST /jobs\n                    • Request: tenant_id, job spec (stages)\n                    • Response: job_definition_id, version\n                • GET /jobs/{job_definition_id}?version=... (default latest)\n                • POST /jobs/{job_definition_id}:newVersion\n                • GET /jobs/{job_definition_id}/versions\n                \n        3. Run submission & lifecycle\n                • POST /runs\n                    • Submits a run for a specific job-definition version. If the same Idempotency-Key is reused by the same tenant, the platform returns the\nexisting run instead of creating a new one.\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}\n                • POST /runs/{run_id}:cancel\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}/stages\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}/events\n        4. Data access / lineage queries: Note all access is based on Header Authorization token Bearer  (from external IdP)\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/current\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/records/{record_id}\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/lineage\n        5. Audit access / reporting: Note all access is based on Header Authorization token Bearer  (from external IdP)\n                • GET /audit-events?run_id=&job_id=&actor=&action=&time_range=&page=\n                • POST/GET /audit-reports\n                • POST(run)/GET/PUT /audit-reports/{report_id}\n\n        6. Retention / purge operations\n                • POST /purge-requests (patient_id, reason_code, scope, requested_by)\n                • GET /purge-requests/{id}\n                • GET /purge-requests?status=...\n                • Purge process is not user facing but per policy it purges data in the background\n                \n\n     Data Plane: (Stateless)\n        Observability\n⸻\n\nData Model and Ownership: writes that change meaning/permissions go through control plane; data plane enforces + reports\n    Control Plane:(Authoritative) \n        JobDefinition(owner job registry):\n            (job_id) unique/system genertated\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            description\n        JobDefinitionVersion(owner job registry):\n            (job_definition_id/job_version_id) unique/version is monotonic and system generated\n            spec_ref (snapshot artifact)\n            spec_hash\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            status  (CURRENT / LEGACY / REVOKED) (“reverted” should be modeled as “a newer version marked CURRENT,” not mutating history)\n        JobRun(owner job Run):\n            (run_id)unique/system generated\n            spec_artifact ( pointer to versioned runtime configuration code as artifact )\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            job_definition_id\n            job_version_id\n            primary_region ( Contract with resource allocation mapping is that resources are multi-region; primary_region gets preference  )\n            max_retry\n            retention_ttl\n            execution_timeout\n        RunIdempotency(owner job Run):\n            (tenant_id, idempotency_key) unique/ idempotency comes from the client, they must manage globally per tenant\n            run_id\n            user_id\n            created_at\n            retention_policy ( must cover retry windows and client retry behavior )\n        TenantSpec(owner Tenant Service):\n            (tenant_id) unique/system generated\n            quota\n            ownership metadata\n        TenantAccess(owner Tenant Service):\n            (tenant_id/principal_id/role_id) unique\n        Role:\n            (tenant_id/role_id) unique\n            scope\n        JobAttempt(owner job Run):\n            (job_attempt_id) unique/system generated\n            run_id\n            status (Pending / Queued / Running / Canceled / Failed)\n            region\n            cluster_id\n            current_retry\n            timestamp\n        StageAttempt(owner job Run):\n            (stage_attempt_id) unique/system generated\n            job_attempt_id\n            status (Pending / Queued / Running / Canceled / Failed)\n            current_retry\n            timestamp\n        Patients(owner Clinical Record Service & PHI) :\n            (patient_id) unique/system generated\n            patient_metadata\n            created_at\n        PurgeRequest(owner Clinical Record Service):\n            id, status, patient_id, reason_code, scope, requested_by\n        BronzeChangeEvent(event_id, tenant_id, patient_id, source_system, payload_ref, schema_version, occurred_at, ingested_at, run_id nullable)        \n        SilverRecords(owner Clinical Record Service  & PHI): (full transformations records land in object store but view index in metadata DB)\n            (record_id) unique/system generated\n            patient_id\n            record_url (object store)\n            last_update_timestamp\n        AuditEvents(owner Audit Service):\n            event_id (unique)\n            tenant_id\n            action( patient_id, record_id, run_id, job_id )\n            resource( region, cluster_id, container_id )\n            actor ( request_id + principal_id )\n            outcome\n            timestamp\n        AuditReports(owner Audit Service):\n            report_id\n            spec ( templated document with prebuilt queries against the audit-event api )            \n\n    Data Plane:\n            JobRunQueue: non-authoritative, TTL, max size, logical partition by region/cluster_id, physical partition by hash run_id\n⸻\n\nHigh Level Components:\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements\n\nIngestion Job Definitions:\n    Create/Read Job (Batch/Near-Real-Time) Ingestion Definitions\n    Create new versions of job definitions; view prior versions\n    Support multi-stage processing( validation -> normalization -> enrichment -> aggregation ) \n    \nIngestion Run Definitions:\n    Submit run referencing a specific Job Definition version with input references\n    cancel a run\n    View/export run event history\n    Get Job Status + per-stage status\n    \nData Access:\n    Query patient records (Curated)\n    Query lineage for a patient record / run\n    Query audit data (who accessed what, when, via which action)\n    Produce Audit reports / exports for a time range and tenant\n\nData Purge Operations:\n    Apply retention policies\n    Execute purge by policy label / patient request\n\nTenant:\n    Create/manage tenants and their scoped resources\n    Manage roles/permissions (scoped to tenant)\n    Manage users/service accounts\n    view tenant configuration change history\n    View/export tenant usage and cost attribution reports    \n    \n\n⸻\n\nNon-Functional Requirements \nAvailability / DR\n    CP SLO: 99.99% (Create/Read Job, Submit/Cancel run, Query)\n    DP SLO: \n        * per cluster availability 99.99%\n        * per-logical-run target 99.999% w/ sequential failover\n        * Failure Classes: component / zone / region; degraded-mode preference: serve traffic > make changes\n    RPO/RTO (for control-plane state only):\n        Submit/Cancel persisted state: RPO 2 minutes\n        Config state (tenant/job): RPO 5 minutes\n        RTO targets: Submit/Cancel 2 hours; Config 6 hours\n\nScale / Geo:\n    Tenants: 100s\n    Job Definitions: 100s\n    Concurrent Jobs: 100s\n    Ingestion Rate(max / avg ): (100,000 / 10,000) records a minute\n    Payload Size(max / avg ): (10mb / 1mb)\n    Data Growth:  10,000 records a minute * 1mb = 10GB / minute\n    Exactly-once processing semantics per logical data submission\n    active/active regions with regional failure handling, multi-region concurrency\n\nLatency(p95 / p50): \n    Ingest-to-Bronze from Kafka: < 30s / < 1s \n    All Indexed Queries: < 1s / < 200ms\n    Job Scheduling: # Counts include non-failover events, +5 minutes for failover\n        SubmitJobRun: < 500ms / < 10ms\n        GetJobRun / status: < 500ms / 10ms\n        Enqueue-to-start (scheduler + dispatch): < 5s / < 1s\n        CancelRun: < 30s / < 10s\n\nSecurity: \n    Strong Authentication and Authorization for each tenant\n    RBAC controls per tenant user for data access; \n    Data is encrypted at rest and in transit\n\nAudit: \n    patient records and lineage(immutable, add (timestamp, user, and on mutation the data column version change))\n    Job and Run Definitions and changes(immutable, w/ timestamp, user, and version change)\n    HIPAA data access(immutable)\n    Data is tagged with Policy Labels for TTL\n \nCost:\n    data retention for all audit and definition by policy label\n    tenant cost show back and quotas \n\nObservability: \n    Golden signals (latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and globally\n    SLO burn-rate paging;\n    Timeseries Cost Spend Graphs per Job\n    Rollback triggers for jobs\n\n\n    \n⸻\n\nScope\n    Assumption:\n        Identity Providers are external\n        Electronic Health Records configuration are assumed to be understood\n            Long-term storage is object storage (provider-managed) and is the system of record for bronze artifacts\n        Out of Scope\n                * User portal, experimentation, producing data, data labeling per policy\n                * Building/testing job artifacts (CI/CD)\n                * Full centralized telemetry ingestion/storage pipeline\n                * Cost-center accounting system (we only produce usage/charge events)\n                * Multi-region concurrent execution of the same logical run (active/active execution)\n                * dynamic cluster registration UI/workflows\n                * Latency for Bronze-to-Silver & Silver-to-Gold is job specific and dependent on the curation workflow\n                * No automatic partial rollback of downstream curated datasets    \n        In Scope:\n            Ingestion from Kafka to Bronze bucket\n            Batch Job Processing from bucket to bucket    \n            PHI level Audit for ETL/ELT workflows\n            Explicits queries for ( patient records/lineage, job definition and execution, and user data access )\n            \n           \n    ⸻\n    \n    Correctness Invariants\n    \n    Tenant Isolation: Tenant-scoped data, compute, and quotas never cross tenant boundaries; all execution and attribution is strictly tenant-scoped. Prevents: data leakage, noisy neighbor incidents, incorrect chargeback.\n    \n    Single Logical Identity via Idempotency: For a given tenant and idempotency key, there is exactly one logical ingestion submission; retries must never create a second logical entity. Prevents: duplicate messages under retries and partitions.\n    \n    Immutable, Versioned Audit Log: All job definition versions, run lifecycle events, patient records, and HIPAA data is append-only within retention window and deletions are policy-driven and themselves audited. \n    \n    Authorization-before-access for PHI: User access controls with least-privilege are required access to data by policy of that data. \n    \n    Lineage completeness: Every served patient record can be traced within the policy retention window. \n    ⸻\n    \nAPI Surface \n    Control Plane(all client-facing):\n        1. Tenant & Identity/Access management \n                • Tenant Scoped\n                    • GET /tenants\n                    • PATCH /tenants/{tenant_id}/settings\n                    • POST /tenants/access # manage role bindings to users_id's\n                • Platform Scoped\n                    • DELETE /tenants/{tenant_id}\n                    • POST /tenants\n        2. Job definition management (versioned)\n                • POST /jobs\n                    • Request: tenant_id, job spec (stages)\n                    • Response: job_definition_id, version\n                • GET /jobs/{job_definition_id}?version=... (default latest)\n                • POST /jobs/{job_definition_id}:newVersion\n                • GET /jobs/{job_definition_id}/versions\n                \n        3. Run submission & lifecycle\n                • POST /runs\n                    • Submits a run for a specific job-definition version. If the same Idempotency-Key is reused by the same tenant, the platform returns the existing run instead of creating a new one.\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}\n                • POST /runs/{run_id}:cancel\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}/stages\n                • GET /runs/{run_id}/events\n        4. Data access / lineage queries: Note all access is based on Header Authorization token Bearer  (from external IdP)\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/current\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/records/{record_id}\n                • GET /query/patients/patient_id/{patient_id}/lineage\n        5. Audit access / reporting: Note all access is based on Header Authorization token Bearer  (from external IdP)\n                • GET /audit-events?run_id=&job_id=&actor=&action=&time_range=&page=\n                • POST/GET /audit-reports\n                • POST(run)/GET/PUT /audit-reports/{report_id}\n\n        6. Retention / purge operations\n                • POST /purge-requests (patient_id, reason_code, scope, requested_by)\n                • GET /purge-requests/{id}\n                • GET /purge-requests?status=...\n                • Purge process is not user facing but per policy it purges data in the background\n                \n\n     Data Plane: (Stateless)\n        Observability\n⸻\n\nData Model and Ownership: writes that change meaning/permissions go through control plane; data plane enforces + reports\n    Control Plane:(Authoritative) \n        JobDefinition(owner job registry):\n            (job_id) unique/system genertated\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            description\n        JobDefinitionVersion(owner job registry):\n            (job_definition_id/job_version_id) unique/version is monotonic and system generated\n            spec_ref (snapshot artifact)\n            spec_hash\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            status  (CURRENT / LEGACY / REVOKED) (“reverted” should be modeled as “a newer version marked CURRENT,” not mutating history)\n        JobRun(owner job Run):\n            (run_id)unique/system generated\n            spec_artifact ( pointer to versioned runtime configuration code as artifact )\n            tenant_id\n            user_id\n            create_timestamp\n            job_definition_id\n            job_version_id\n            primary_region ( Contract with resource allocation mapping is that resources are multi-region; primary_region gets preference  )\n            max_retry\n            retention_ttl\n            execution_timeout\n        RunIdempotency(owner job Run):\n            (tenant_id, idempotency_key) unique/ idempotency comes from the client, they must manage globally per tenant\n            run_id\n            user_id\n            created_at\n            retention_policy ( must cover retry windows and client retry behavior )\n        TenantSpec(owner Tenant Service):\n            (tenant_id) unique/system generated\n            quota\n            ownership metadata\n        TenantAccess(owner Tenant Service):\n            (tenant_id/principal_id/role_id) unique\n        Role:\n            (tenant_id/role_id) unique\n            scope\n        JobAttempt(owner job Run):\n            (job_attempt_id) unique/system generated\n            run_id\n            status (Pending / Queued / Running / Canceled / Failed)\n            region\n            cluster_id\n            current_retry\n            timestamp\n        StageAttempt(owner job Run):\n            (stage_attempt_id) unique/system generated\n            job_attempt_id\n            status (Pending / Queued / Running / Canceled / Failed)\n            current_retry\n            timestamp\n        Patients(owner Clinical Record Service & PHI) :\n            (patient_id) unique/system generated\n            patient_metadata\n            created_at\n        PurgeRequest(owner Clinical Record Service):\n            id, status, patient_id, reason_code, scope, requested_by\n        BronzeChangeEvent(event_id, tenant_id, patient_id, source_system, payload_ref, schema_version, occurred_at, ingested_at, run_id nullable)        \n        SilverRecords(owner Clinical Record Service  & PHI): (full transformations records land in object store but view index in metadata DB)\n            (record_id) unique/system generated\n            patient_id\n            record_url (object store)\n            last_update_timestamp\n        AuditEvents(owner Audit Service):\n            event_id (unique)\n            tenant_id\n            action( patient_id, record_id, run_id, job_id )\n            resource( region, cluster_id, container_id )\n            actor ( request_id + principal_id )\n            outcome\n            timestamp\n        AuditReports(owner Audit Service):\n            report_id\n            spec ( templated document with prebuilt queries against the audit-event api )            \n\n    Data Plane:\n            JobRunQueue: non-authoritative, TTL, max size, logical partition by region/cluster_id, physical partition by hash run_id\n⸻\n\nHigh Level Components:\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
