    {
      "id": "ntt7Xp_CaUnHV8UoLbXPC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -3168.7894019168994,
      "y": 4673.445645726534,
      "width": 1753.4895806738014,
      "height": 975,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9O",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 259365192,
      "version": 1054,
      "versionNonce": 1045388616,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769096616358,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Flow: Run Submission (End-to-End)\n        1. API Gateway\n            Authenticates the caller and forwards the request with principal context.\n            No state written.\n        2. Tenant Service\n            Authorizes the caller for the target tenant and operation.\n            Invariant enforced: Tenant Isolation.\n            No state written.\n        3. Run Submission Service\n            Validates the request and checks the Idempotency-Key against the Run Registry.\n                • If a matching entry exists for the tenant, returns the existing run_id.\n                • Otherwise proceeds with run creation.\n            Invariant enforced: Single Logical Identity via Idempotency.\n        4. Run Registry (Authoritative)\n            Atomically persists:\n                • Logical run identity and initial run state\n                • Idempotency mapping\n                • Initial run attempt (status = PENDING)\n            Emits an audit event for the state change.\n            Invariant enforced: Immutable, Versioned Audit Log.\n        5. Dispatch Service\n            Receives a durable dispatch request from the control plane, validates the run is not canceled, and selects an eligible execution target.\n            No authoritative state change.\n        6. Execution Workers (Data Plane)\n            Consume the dispatched request and execute the run within tenant-scoped quotas and isolation boundaries.\n            Invariant enforced: Tenant Isolation.\n        7. Run Registry\n            Receives status updates from execution (QUEUED → RUNNING → SUCCESS/FAILED/CANCELED) and persists run and attempt state transitions.\n            Emits audit events for lifecycle changes.\n            Invariant enforced: Immutable, Versioned Audit Log.\n        8. Ingestion / Transformation Execution\n            • Streaming ingestion writes bronze data to object storage.\n            • Batch transformations read from bronze and produce curated outputs.\n            Audit events are emitted for data access and transformation actions.\n        9. Clinical Record Service\n            Persists PHI payloads to object storage and updates metadata indexes used for query and lineage.\n            Invariant enforced: Authorization-before-access for PHI, Lineage Completeness.\n        10. Completion\n            Run reaches a terminal state (SUCCESS / FAILED / CANCELED) and is observable via status, lineage, and audit queries.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Flow: Run Submission (End-to-End)\n        1. API Gateway\n            Authenticates the caller and forwards the request with principal context.\n            No state written.\n        2. Tenant Service\n            Authorizes the caller for the target tenant and operation.\n            Invariant enforced: Tenant Isolation.\n            No state written.\n        3. Run Submission Service\n            Validates the request and checks the Idempotency-Key against the Run Registry.\n                • If a matching entry exists for the tenant, returns the existing run_id.\n                • Otherwise proceeds with run creation.\n            Invariant enforced: Single Logical Identity via Idempotency.\n        4. Run Registry (Authoritative)\n            Atomically persists:\n                • Logical run identity and initial run state\n                • Idempotency mapping\n                • Initial run attempt (status = PENDING)\n            Emits an audit event for the state change.\n            Invariant enforced: Immutable, Versioned Audit Log.\n        5. Dispatch Service\n            Receives a durable dispatch request from the control plane, validates the run is not canceled, and selects an eligible execution target.\n            No authoritative state change.\n        6. Execution Workers (Data Plane)\n            Consume the dispatched request and execute the run within tenant-scoped quotas and isolation boundaries.\n            Invariant enforced: Tenant Isolation.\n        7. Run Registry\n            Receives status updates from execution (QUEUED → RUNNING → SUCCESS/FAILED/CANCELED) and persists run and attempt state transitions.\n            Emits audit events for lifecycle changes.\n            Invariant enforced: Immutable, Versioned Audit Log.\n        8. Ingestion / Transformation Execution\n            • Streaming ingestion writes bronze data to object storage.\n            • Batch transformations read from bronze and produce curated outputs.\n            Audit events are emitted for data access and transformation actions.\n        9. Clinical Record Service\n            Persists PHI payloads to object storage and updates metadata indexes used for query and lineage.\n            Invariant enforced: Authorization-before-access for PHI, Lineage Completeness.\n        10. Completion\n            Run reaches a terminal state (SUCCESS / FAILED / CANCELED) and is observable via status, lineage, and audit queries.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
